  "Custom tier": "Izinga elizenzele",
  "Daily Nous reports on a retracted Journal of Medical Ethics submission containing multiple fabricated, AI-hallucinated references — complete with fake university affiliations and defunct email addresses — that the author reportedly left uncorrected even after being given a chance to fix proofs. The piece contrasts this with Bioethics, whose automated reference-checking would have caught the problem, and argues the real bottleneck isn't detection technology (one commenter's script flagged the fake citations in under a minute) but unpaid reviewer labor and publishing incentives that reward throughput over scrutiny.": "I-Daily Nous ibika ngesibiko esihoxisiwe se-Journal of Medical Ethics esasinemithombo eminingi eyenziwe ngokuqamba amanga, ecatshangwe yi-AI — kanye nokuhlangana namanyuvesi angekho ngempela namakheli e-imeyili angasasebenzi — okubikwa ukuthi umbhali wayishiya ingalungiswanga ngisho nangemuva kokunikwa ithuba lokulungisa amaphutha. Lo mbhalo uwuqhathanisa neJenali i-Bioethics, okuyilapho ukuhlolwa ngokuzenzakalela kwemithombo okwakuzoyithola inkinga, futhi uphikisana ngokuthi umgoqo wangempela akusiyona ubuchwepheshe bokuthola (isikripthi somuntu owaphawula sathola ukucaphuna okungamanga ngaphansi komzuzu owodwa) kodwa umsebenzi wababukezi ongakhokhelwa kanye nezikhuthazo zokushicilela ezivuza inani kunokuhlolisisa.",
  "Data free-riding vs. trillion-dollar AI valuations": "Ukusebenzisa idatha kungakhokhi vs. izilinganiso zamanani e-AI ezingamazigidigidi zamadola",
  "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI": "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI",
  "Demis Hassabis proposed a FINRA-style regulator for frontier model releases: labs would submit models for review up to 30 days before deployment, voluntary at first, with a path toward mandatory compliance in the US market.": "UDemis Hassabis uphakamise umlawuli ohlobo lwe-FINRA wokukhishwa kwamamodeli asesikhondlweni: amalabhorethri ayeyothumela amamodeli ukuze abukezwe kuze kube izinsuku ezingu-30 ngaphambi kokusetshenziswa, ngokuzithandela ekuqaleni, kunendlela eya ekuthotshelweni okuphoqelelwe emakethe yase-US.",
  "Denied": "Kwenqatshiwe",
  "Deployable policy starter template": "Ithempuleti lokuqala lenqubomgomo elingasetshenziswa",
  "Deployable policy starter template at /downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — a minimal static site with the full machine-readable layer, ready for Cloudflare Pages or any static host.": "Ithempuleti lokuqala lenqubomgomo elingasetshenziswa ku-/downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — isayithi encane engaguquki enohlaka olugcwele olufundeka yimishini, elilungele iCloudflare Pages noma noma iyiphi indawo yokuhweba engaguquki.",
  "Deploying machine-readable policies on your site": "Ukusebenzisa izinqubomgomo ezifundeka yimishini kusayithi yakho",
  "Disclaimer": "Isexwayiso",
  "Distinct from human UI, SEO, or plain APIs, the AI Ingestion & Capability Layer gives websites a machine-facing architecture: a Manifest Layer (entry points like /llms.txt and /ai/manifest.json), a Corpus Layer (machine-readable knowledge), a Capability Layer (agent-callable tools), and a Governance Layer (provenance, licensing, versioning). Static-first, upgradeable toward APIs and MCP. Note: in this paper AICL names the ingestion architecture; on this site's protocol pages AICL refers to the AI Content Licensing Layer.": "Ihlukile kusayithi ye-UI yabantu, i-SEO, noma ama-API alula, i-AI Ingestion & Capability Layer inikeza amawebhusayithi isakhiwo esibhekiswe kumishini: Uhlaka Lwemanifesti (izindawo zokungena ezifana ne-/llms.txt kanye ne-/ai/manifest.json), Uhlaka Lwe-Corpus (ulwazi olufundeka yimishini), Uhlaka Lwekhono (amathuluzi angabizwa yi-ejenti), kanye Nohlaka Lokulawulwa (umsuka, ukunikezwa kwelayisensi, izinguqulo). Ligxile kokungaguquki kuqala, lingathuthukiswa liye kuma-API ne-MCP. Qaphela: kuleli phepha i-AICL iqamba isakhiwo sokumunca; emakhasini amaphrothokholi ale sayithi i-AICL ibhekisa Kuhlaka Lokunikezwa Kwelayisensi Kokuqukethwe Kwe-AI.",
  "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm": "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm",
  "Docs": "Imibhalo",
  "Docs / Examples": "Imibhalo / Izibonelo",
  "Document library": "Umtapo Wamadokhumenti",
  "Does AI have rights — and which framings are even coherent?": "Ngabe i-AI inamalungelo — futhi yiziphi izindlela zokucabanga ezinengqondo?",
