  "read_access — whether AI may fetch and read the content": "read_access — ukuthi ngabe i-AI ingalanda futhi ifunde okuqukethwe",
  "redistribution — republishing or redistributing content or derivatives": "redistribution — ukushicilela kabusha noma ukusatshalalisa kabusha okuqukethwe noma imiphumela evela kukho",
  "research pages & whitepapers": "amakhasi ocwaningo namaphepha amhlophe",
  "robots.txt and llms.txt govern access and visibility, not learning depth or use permissions. AIRS proposes expressing AI rights as a proportional, use-specific spectrum across ten dimensions — access, indexing, inference input, embedding, training, fine-tuning, distillation, memory, output, attribution/compensation. AILP translates this into /ai/rights-spectrum.json, letting creators declare granular permissions with compensation models ranging from free through license-required to revenue share.": "I-robots.txt ne-llms.txt zilawula ukufinyelela nokubonakala, hhayi ubunzulu bokufunda noma izimvume zokusetshenziswa. I-AIRS iphakamisa ukuveza amalungelo e-AI njengesipektramu esilinganayo, esiqondene nokusetshenziswa, kuzo zonke izici eziyishumi — ukufinyelela, ukuhlelwa ngezinkomba, okufakwayo kokuqagela, i-embedding, ukuqeqeshwa, i-fine-tuning, i-distillation, inkumbulo, umphumela, ukuboniswa komthombo/inkokhelo. I-AILP iguqula lokhu ibe i-/ai/rights-spectrum.json, ivumela abadali ukuthi bamemezele izimvume ezicophelele ngamamodeli enkokhelo asukela kokumahhala kuya kokudinga ilayisensi kuya ekwabelaneni ngenzuzo.",
